1. Inſinuate thy ſelf into their affections. Let them know, that thou haſt no deſign upon them, but to make them happy. Indeavour to perſwade them that thou haſt no private end, only their everlaſting good. Winde into their hearts, ſcrew thy ſelf into their affections, and thou haſt done half thy work.Max. Tyr. diſſert. 10. Ed. Heinſ. 1607.
                [
