                The caſe varies not in ſpiritual matters. Labour then to gain their love, their good eſteem, and the work will thrive beyond expectation.

THeſe words may well be treated on without much Preface,Rom. 16.24. 1. Cor. 16.23, 24. 2 Ep. 13.14. Gal. 6.18. there being nothing in them, which ſpeaks any dependance upon, or connexion with any thing that went before. Some form of Benediction we finde uſed by this Great Apoſtle, at the concluſion of every Epiſtle; and accordingly having driven his excellent deſign in this to the Church of Epheſus, to a full period or iſſue; hee firſt makes an affectionate addreſs to God, and to the Mediator in their behalf, v. 23. Grace be to the Brethren, and love with Faith from God the Father, and the Lord Jeſus Chriſt, and then leaves his Apoſtolical Benediction upon them, v. 24. Grace be with all them, that love our Lord Jeſus Chriſt in ſincerity: Or, The bleſſing of the Eternal God be upon all the ſincere-hearted Chriſtians amongſt you, for ſo I look upon the latter words of the verſe, as a Periphraſis of all real Chriſtians; Love to Chriſt being as eſſential to the Chriſtian, as the Rational Soul is to the man. The only difficulty in the words, that will require our ſtay, is to inquire, what is meant by [
